# Markdown Authoring Standards

- Use exactly one H1 title per file.
- Keep heading hierarchy consistent (`##`, then `###`; avoid skipping levels).
- Prefer short sections with descriptive headings.
- Use bulleted lists for scannable procedures and checklists.
- Use fenced code blocks with language tags for commands/snippets.
- Use descriptive link text instead of "click here".
- Keep terminology consistent with `docs/glossary.md`.
- For process/critical docs, include owner, last reviewed, source, and confidence.

# Retrieval-Friendly Writing

- Keep each section focused on one idea or one procedure.
- Put definitions before edge cases.
- Include explicit names (team, system, tool) rather than pronouns.
- For policy/process docs, include effective date and owner where known.
